SIMPLE: neodymium
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neodymium
<hw>Ne`o*dym"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. Dee
<er>Neo-</er>, and <er>Didymium</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The
chemical element of atomic number 60, one of the <isa>rare earth</isa>
elements. Symbol <it>Nd</it>. Atomic weight 144.27.</def> <note>It is a
rare metallic element occurring in combination with cerium, lanthanum,
and other rare metals, and forming amethyst-colored salts. It was
originally thought to be part of a supposed new element
<partof>didymium</partof>, obtained from cerite in 1843. Later this was
resolved into two elements, neodymium and praesodymium by <person>von
Welsbach</person> in 1885. It is chiefly trivalent. It is a faintly
yellow metal.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

